item.title: Caitlin add a quote by John F. Kennedy
item.description: "The Chinese use two brush strokes to write the word 'crisis.' One brush stroke stands for danger; the other for opportunity. In a crisis, be aware of the danger--but recognize the opportunity." -- John F. Kennedy

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Francois de La Rochefoucauld
item.description: "One cannot answer for his courage when he has never been in danger." -- Francois de La Rochefoucauld

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Nelson Mandela
item.description: "I learned that courage was not the absence of fear, but the triumph over it. The brave man is not he who does not feel afraid, but he who conquers that fear." -- Nelson Mandela

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Chrostopher Logue
item.description: "Come to the edge.' 'We can't. We're afraid.' 'Come to the edge.' 'We can't. We will fall!' 'Come to the edge.' And they came. And he pushed them. And they flew." -- Chrostopher Logue

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Winston S. Churchill
item.description: "Success is stumbling from failure to failure with no loss of enthusiasm." -- Winston S. Churchill

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Marc A. Pitman
item.description: "Life's short. Live passionately." -- Marc A. Pitman

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Bernard M. Baruch
item.description: "Be who you are and say what you feel, because those who mind don't matter, and those who matter don't mind." -- Bernard M. Baruch

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "You know you're in love when you can't fall asleep because reality is finally better than your dreams." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Albert Camus
item.description: "In the depth of winter, I finally learned that within me there lay an invincible summer." -- Albert Camus

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Victor Hugo
item.description: "People do not lack strength, they lack will." -- Victor Hugo

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "If things start happening, don't worry, don't stew, just go right along and you'll start happening too." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Fantasy is a necessary ingredient in living, it's a way of looking at life through the wrong end of a telescope." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Think left and think right and think low and think high. Oh, the thinks you can think up if only you try!" -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Only you can control your future." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Look at me! Look at me! Look at me NOW! It is fun to have fun But you have to know how." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Think and wonder, wonder and think." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by Mae West
item.description: "You only live once, but if you do it right, once is enough." -- Mae West

item.title: Caitlin add a quote by H. Jackson Brown Jr.
item.description: "Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed by the things that you didn't do than by the ones you did do. So throw off the bowlines. Sail away from the safe harbor. Catch the trade winds in your sails. Explore. Dream. Discover." -- H. Jackson Brown Jr.
